text: Abdulrahman Al Faihan (born 24 June 1986) is a Kuwaiti sport shooter who competed in the Men's Trap Shooting competition in the 2016 Summer Olympics. He participated within the Independent Olympic Athletes team. ==Career== In January 2016 he won a gold medal and an Olympic quota place while competing under the ISSF flag at the 2016 Asian Olympic Qualifying Tournament in New Delhi, India. The IOC had imposed a suspension on the Kuwait Olympic Committee in October 2015 as a result of legislation brought in by the Kuwaiti government that could have affected the autonomy of sporting organizations in the country. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:Living people Category:1986 births Category:Olympic shooters of Kuwait Category:Shooters at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic shooters as Independent Olympic Participants Category:Shooters at the 2006 Asian Games Category:Shooters at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Shooters at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Shooters at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Kuwait Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Kuwait Category:Asian Games medalists in shooting Category:Medalists at the 2006 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Kuwaiti male sport shooters Category:Trap and double trap shooters
